						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka [8]22</hi> (<hi rend="italic">mistake for</hi> 824), <hi rend="bold">Dundubhi, Māgha, śu. 5. Thursday, Uttarāshāḍha, siddhi-yōga (= A.D. 903, January 6, Thursday)</hi> and belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">[Akāla]varshadēva (i.e., Kṛishṇa II).</hi> It records the installation of a god (name lost) and a grant of land to the same.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Indian Antiquary,</hi> Vol. XII, p. 221.</p>						

						</summary>
